# VM Operations

## Environment

- **VM IP**: 192.168.8.65, user: `x`
- **OS**: Artix Linux, init: dinit (not systemd — use `dinitctl`, not `systemctl`)
- **Project path**: `/home/x/dev/model-archival/local/`
- **Screen session**: `archiver` (`screen -S archiver bash run.sh --all`)

## Disk layout

| Label | Device | Mount | Size | Role |
|-------|--------|-------|------|------|
| D1 | /dev/sdc | /mnt/models/d1 | 5.5 TB | Large models + `.tmp/` scratch |
| D2 | /dev/sdd | /mnt/models/d2 | 2.7 TB | Mid-size models + Tier D |
| D3 | /dev/sde | /mnt/models/d3 | 2.7 TB | GGUF quants |
| D5 | /dev/sdb | /mnt/models/d5 | 916 GB | Metadata, logs, state |

In-progress downloads land in `D1/.tmp/` — never on D5 or root SSD.

## Before rebooting — always stop gracefully

```bash
bash /home/x/dev/model-archival/local/stop.sh   # wait for "stopped cleanly"
# then reboot — skipping this can corrupt D1/D2 (requires fsck to fix)
```

## If drives not mounted after reboot

```bash
sudo bash /home/x/dev/model-archival/local/deploy/vm-mount-disks.sh
```

## If a drive shows "Structure needs cleaning"

```bash
sudo fsck.ext4 -y /dev/sdXN   # fix filesystem
sudo mount /mnt/models/dN     # then remount
```

## VPN (Surfshark via OpenVPN)

```bash
# Status check
surfshark-vpn status 2>/dev/null; curl -s https://ipinfo.io | grep -E '"ip"|"org"'
# Should show: "AS9009 M247 Europe SRL" — not your ISP

# Connect (if not auto-started by dinit)
sudo openvpn --config /etc/openvpn/client/surfshark/us-nyc.prod.surfshark.com_udp.ovpn \
             --auth-user-pass /etc/openvpn/client/surfshark.auth \
             --daemon --log /var/log/surfshark-openvpn.log

# Auto-starts via dinit: /etc/dinit.d/boot.d/surfshark-vpn
```

Note: Surfshark AUR CLI (`surfshark-vpn` binary v1.1.0) is broken — use OpenVPN directly.
Note: Surfshark flatpak GUI fails with "No internet connection" on connman systems — use OpenVPN.

## Monitor downloads

```bash
screen -S archiver -X hardcopy /tmp/s.txt && cat /tmp/s.txt   # snapshot screen
watch -n 30 cat /mnt/models/d5/STATUS.md                       # live status file
```
